You should use `map` instead of `tap`.
`tap` does not return a value, so it means you will dispatch the service&#39;s result back to the store which is causing the invalid action error. With `map` you transform the service response to a valid NgRx Action.

The code you&#39;re showing, is valid so my guess would be that something else is causing the infinite loop.

```
 switchMap(() =&gt; this.roleService.getAllRoles().pipe(
   map(roles =&gt; {
     return new AllRolesLoaded({ roles });
   }),
   catchError((error) =&gt; of(new ErrorLoadRole(error)))
 )),
```

I believe this effect is the culprit:

    @Effect()
    init$: Observable&lt;RoleActions&gt; = defer(() =&gt; {
      return of(new RequestLoadRoles());
    });

remove it and in the constructor of the service do

    this.store.dispatch(new RequestLoadRoles());
PS .map() is used to transform the data of the pipeline (that&#39;s what you need: transform list of roles into a AllRolesLoaded action), and .tap() acts like a side effect, so the pipeline is not actually influenced

